def has_light_in_room(room:item):
    # Function to check if there is at least one light in a specified room
    symbol has_light=exists o: item : is_light(o) and inside(o, room) and is_on(o)
    return has_light

behavior turn_on_light(light:item):
    body:
        achieve is_on(light)
        # Turn on the light

behavior __goal__():

        bind bathroom: item where:
            is_bathroom(bathroom) and id[bathroom]==1

        bind bedroom: item where:

        bind dining_room: item where:
            is_dining_room(dining_room) and id[dining_room]==201

        if not has_light_in_room(bathroom):
            bind light: item where:
                is_light(light) and inside(light, bathroom)
            turn_on_light(light)
        
        if not has_light_in_room(bedroom):
            bind light: item where:
                is_light(light) and inside(light, bedroom)
            turn_on_light(light)
        
        if not has_light_in_room(dining_room):
            bind light: item where:
                is_light(light) and inside(light, dining_room)
            turn_on_light(light)

def has_light_off(room: item):
    # Function to check if there is a light that is off in a specified room
    symbol light_off=exists light: item : is_light(light) and is_off(light) and inside(light, room)
    return light_off

behavior turn_on_light(room: item):
    body:
        bind light: item where:

        # Select the light in the room that is off
        achieve is_on(light)
        # Turn the selected light on
